items.title: Incoming German Chancellor Merz vows reforms and investments as parties sign coalition agreement
items.description: Germany's incoming Chancellor Friedrich Merz and the country's new cabinet are set to take office Tuesday.

items.title: Trump takes credit for 'good parts' of economy, blames 'bad parts' on Biden
items.description: Last week, Trump put the onus on Biden for the economy contracting in the first quarter of the year.

items.title: NPR and PBS CEOs say they'll challenge Trump administration over federal funding cuts
items.description: The CEOs of NPR and PBS said on Sunday's "Face the Nation" they will challenge Trump's executive order to end federal funding to the organizations.

items.title: Trump posts AI-generated photo of himself dressed as the pope
items.description: President Trump earlier this year jokingly called himself a "king" after he moved to end the congestion pricing program in New York City.

items.title: Waltz used Signal-like app at White House day before ouster as national security advisor
items.description: President Trump recently discouraged the use of the Signal app after controversy over a group chat of administration officials detailed military plans...
